---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import MoonPhaseCalculator from '../components/MoonPhaseCalculator.jsx';
---

<Layout
	title="Moon Phase Calculator — Today's Moon Phase & Any Date | Clockr"
	description="Find the moon phase for today or any date. See illumination, lunar cycle day, and days until the next full moon or new moon."
	category="seasons"
>
	<div class="sc-page">
		<div class="sc-header">
			<div class="sc-eyebrow">
				<span class="sc-eyebrow-square" aria-hidden="true"></span>
				SEASONS
			</div>
			<h1 class="sc-title">
				<span class="sc-gradient">Moon Phase Calculator</span>
			</h1>
			<p class="sc-subtitle">Find the moon phase for any date</p>
		</div>

		<MoonPhaseCalculator client:load />

		<!-- HOW IT WORKS -->
		<section class="sc-how">
			<h2 class="sc-section-title">How it works</h2>
			<div class="sc-how-card">
				<p>
					The Moon does not produce its own light — we see it because sunlight
					reflects off its surface. As the Moon orbits Earth, the angle between
					the Sun, Earth, and Moon changes, so the portion of the lit side we can
					see from Earth changes too. One complete cycle from new moon to new moon
					takes about 29.5 days, which is why moon phases follow a predictable
					monthly rhythm.
				</p>
				<p>
					This calculator uses a standard astronomical approximation: a known new
					moon on 6 January 2000 as a reference point, plus a lunar cycle length
					of 29.53059 days. For any date, it works out how many days have elapsed
					since that reference, divides by the cycle length, and finds the
					position within the current cycle. From that position it derives the
					illumination percentage, phase name, and estimated dates of the next
					full and new moons — no API or telescope required.
				</p>
				<p>
					Moon phases have long been used as a practical calendar in farming,
					fishing, and navigation, and they still influence coastal tides
					(alongside the Sun). Many cultures mark lunar festivals and folklore
					around the full moon. This tool gives a quick mathematical snapshot;
					for precise astronomical times to the minute, observatories use
					orbital models that account for the Moon's elliptical path.
				</p>
			</div>
		</section>

		<!-- FAQ -->
		<section class="sc-faq">
			<h2 class="sc-section-title">Frequently asked questions</h2>
			<div class="sc-faq-list">
				<details class="sc-faq-item">
					<summary class="sc-faq-question">What is the moon phase today?</summary>
					<div class="sc-faq-answer">
						<p>
							Select &ldquo;Today&apos;s moon phase&rdquo; at the top of this page
							to see the current phase automatically — including the phase name,
							illumination percentage, and how many days until the next full or
							new moon. The result updates for the current calendar date.
						</p>
					</div>
				</details>
				<details class="sc-faq-item">
					<summary class="sc-faq-question">How are moon phases calculated?</summary>
					<div class="sc-faq-answer">
						<p>
							Clockr uses a synodic month length of 29.53059 days and a reference
							new moon on 6 January 2000. The number of days between your chosen
							date and that reference is divided by the cycle length; the
							remainder gives the Moon&apos;s age in the current cycle. Illumination
							is derived from that age using a cosine formula, and phase names
							follow standard waxing and waning ranges.
						</p>
					</div>
				</details>
				<details class="sc-faq-item">
					<summary class="sc-faq-question">How long is a lunar cycle?</summary>
					<div class="sc-faq-answer">
						<p>
							A synodic month — the time from one new moon to the next — averages
							about 29.53 days (29 days, 12 hours, and 44 minutes). That is
							slightly longer than the Moon&apos;s orbital period around Earth
							because Earth is also moving around the Sun, so the Sun-Moon angle
							takes longer to repeat.
						</p>
					</div>
				</details>
				<details class="sc-faq-item">
					<summary class="sc-faq-question">What is a full moon?</summary>
					<div class="sc-faq-answer">
						<p>
							A full moon occurs when the Moon is on the opposite side of Earth
							from the Sun, so nearly the entire face we see is lit. In this
							calculator, full moon corresponds to roughly 100% illumination, at
							about the midpoint of the 29.5-day lunar cycle.
						</p>
					</div>
				</details>
				<details class="sc-faq-item">
					<summary class="sc-faq-question">What is a new moon?</summary>
					<div class="sc-faq-answer">
						<p>
							At new moon, the Moon sits between Earth and the Sun. The side
							facing us is in shadow, so the Moon is barely visible — often not
							at all without special conditions. A new cycle begins at this
							point; the visible portion then grows (waxes) toward the first
							quarter and full moon.
						</p>
					</div>
				</details>
				<details class="sc-faq-item">
					<summary class="sc-faq-question">Does the moon phase affect tides?</summary>
					<div class="sc-faq-answer">
						<p>
							Yes. The Moon&apos;s gravity is the main driver of ocean tides on
							Earth. Spring tides (higher highs and lower lows) tend to occur
							around new and full moons when the Sun and Moon align; neap tides
							(milder) occur around the first and last quarters. Local geography
							and weather also shape what you see at the coast.
						</p>
					</div>
				</details>
			</div>
		</section>

		<!-- RELATED TOOLS -->
		<div class="sc-related">
			<h3 class="sc-related-title">Related tools</h3>
			<div class="sc-related-grid">
				<a href="/season-countdown" class="sc-related-card"
					><span class="sc-related-name">Season Countdown</span></a
				>
				<a href="/year-progress" class="sc-related-card"
					><span class="sc-related-name">Year Progress Bar</span></a
				>
				<a href="/days-until-halloween" class="sc-related-card"
					><span class="sc-related-name">Days Until Halloween</span></a
				>
				<a href="/days-until-christmas" class="sc-related-card"
					><span class="sc-related-name">Days Until Christmas</span></a
				>
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>
</Layout>

<style is:global>
	.sc-page {
		max-width: 800px;
		margin: 0 auto;
		padding: 60px 24px;
	}

	.sc-header {
		text-align: center;
		margin-bottom: 32px;
	}

	.sc-eyebrow {
		display: inline-flex;
		align-items: center;
		gap: 8px;
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 12px;
		font-weight: 700;
		letter-spacing: 3px;
		text-transform: uppercase;
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #2d6a4f, #74b49b);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
		margin-bottom: 16px;
	}

	.sc-eyebrow-square {
		width: 8px;
		height: 8px;
		border-radius: 2px;
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #2d6a4f, #74b49b);
		flex-shrink: 0;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: initial;
	}

	.sc-title {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 64px;
		font-weight: 900;
		letter-spacing: -3px;
		line-height: 1.05;
		margin-bottom: 16px;
	}

	.sc-gradient {
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #2d6a4f, #74b49b);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
	}

	.sc-subtitle {
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 16px;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.5);
		line-height: 1.6;
	}

	.sc-section-title {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 20px;
		font-weight: 700;
		color: #fff;
		margin-bottom: 16px;
	}

	.sc-how {
		margin-bottom: 48px;
	}

	.sc-how-card {
		background: #0c0c0c;
		border: 1px solid rgba(45, 106, 79, 0.15);
		border-radius: 14px;
		padding: 24px;
	}

	.sc-how-card p {
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 15px;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.55);
		line-height: 1.7;
		margin: 0 0 16px;
	}

	.sc-how-card p:last-child {
		margin-bottom: 0;
	}

	.sc-faq {
		margin-bottom: 48px;
	}

	.sc-faq-list {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		gap: 8px;
	}

	.sc-faq-item {
		background: #0c0c0c;
		border: 1px solid rgba(45, 106, 79, 0.15);
		border-radius: 14px;
		overflow: hidden;
	}

	.sc-faq-question {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 15px;
		font-weight: 600;
		padding: 18px 24px;
		cursor: pointer;
		list-style: none;
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #2d6a4f, #74b49b);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
	}

	.sc-faq-question::-webkit-details-marker {
		display: none;
	}

	.sc-faq-question::after {
		content: '+';
		float: right;
		font-size: 18px;
		font-weight: 700;
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #2d6a4f, #74b49b);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
	}

	.sc-faq-item[open] .sc-faq-question::after {
		content: '−';
	}

	.sc-faq-answer {
		padding: 0 24px 18px;
	}

	.sc-faq-answer p {
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 14px;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.55);
		line-height: 1.7;
		margin: 0;
	}

	.sc-related {
		border-top: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.06);
		padding-top: 40px;
	}

	.sc-related-title {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 20px;
		font-weight: 700;
		color: #fff;
		margin-bottom: 16px;
	}

	.sc-related-grid {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
		gap: 12px;
	}

	.sc-related-card {
		background: #0c0c0c;
		border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.06);
		border-radius: 12px;
		padding: 20px 16px;
		text-align: center;
		text-decoration: none;
		transition: border-color 0.2s ease;
	}

	.sc-related-card:hover {
		border-color: rgba(45, 106, 79, 0.4);
	}

	.sc-related-name {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 14px;
		font-weight: 600;
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #2d6a4f, #74b49b);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
	}

	/* Moon Phase Calculator tool */
	.mpc-tool {
		margin-bottom: 48px;
	}

	.mpc-mode-toggle {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
		gap: 12px;
		margin-bottom: 24px;
	}

	.mpc-mode-btn {
		padding: 14px 16px;
		background: rgba(12, 12, 12, 0.6);
		border: 1px solid rgba(45, 106, 79, 0.25);
		border-radius: 12px;
		cursor: pointer;
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 14px;
		font-weight: 700;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.55);
		transition:
			border-color 0.2s ease,
			background 0.2s ease,
			box-shadow 0.2s ease;
	}

	.mpc-mode-btn:hover {
		border-color: rgba(116, 180, 155, 0.5);
		background: rgba(45, 106, 79, 0.08);
	}

	.mpc-mode-btn--active {
		border-color: rgba(116, 180, 155, 0.7);
		background: rgba(45, 106, 79, 0.15);
		box-shadow: 0 0 24px rgba(45, 106, 79, 0.2);
		color: #fff;
		background-image: linear-gradient(135deg, #2d6a4f, #74b49b);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
	}

	.mpc-date-wrap {
		max-width: 320px;
		margin: 0 auto 24px;
	}

	.mpc-hint {
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 14px;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.4);
		text-align: center;
		margin: 0;
	}

	.mpc-hero-band {
		display: flex;
		align-items: center;
		justify-content: center;
		width: 100vw;
		margin-left: calc(50% - 50vw);
		padding: 48px 24px 56px;
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #0d1f17, #1a2e24);
		border-top: 1px solid rgba(45, 106, 79, 0.25);
		border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(45, 106, 79, 0.25);
		overflow: hidden;
		position: relative;
	}

	.mpc-hero-decor {
		position: absolute;
		inset: 0;
		pointer-events: none;
		user-select: none;
	}

	.mpc-float-emoji {
		position: absolute;
		display: inline-block;
		line-height: 1;
		transform: rotate(var(--rotation, 0deg));
		animation: mpc-float 4s ease-in-out infinite;
		opacity: 0.9;
	}

	.mpc-float-emoji--right {
		left: auto;
	}

	@keyframes mpc-float {
		0%,
		100% {
			transform: translateY(0) rotate(var(--rotation, 0deg));
		}
		33% {
			transform: translateY(-10px) rotate(calc(var(--rotation, 0deg) - 3deg));
		}
		66% {
			transform: translateY(-5px) rotate(calc(var(--rotation, 0deg) + 3deg));
		}
	}

	@media (max-width: 600px) {
		.mpc-float-emoji {
			opacity: 0.35;
		}

		.sc-title {
			font-size: 44px;
			letter-spacing: -2px;
		}

		.sc-related-grid {
			grid-template-columns: 1fr;
		}
	}

	.mpc-hero-centre {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		align-items: center;
		text-align: center;
		position: relative;
		z-index: 1;
		width: 100%;
		max-width: 560px;
	}

	.mpc-result-date {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 15px;
		font-weight: 600;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.6);
		margin: 0 0 20px;
	}

	.mpc-moon-display {
		font-size: clamp(72px, 18vw, 120px);
		line-height: 1;
		margin-bottom: 16px;
		filter: drop-shadow(0 0 32px rgba(116, 180, 155, 0.25));
	}

	.mpc-phase-name {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: clamp(28px, 5vw, 40px);
		font-weight: 900;
		letter-spacing: -1px;
		line-height: 1.1;
		margin: 0 0 8px;
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #2d6a4f, #74b49b);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
	}

	.mpc-illumination {
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 18px;
		font-weight: 600;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.65);
		margin: 0 0 32px;
	}

	.mpc-cycle-bar-wrap {
		width: 100%;
		margin-bottom: 32px;
	}

	.mpc-cycle-bar-track {
		position: relative;
		height: 10px;
		background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.08);
		border-radius: 999px;
		overflow: visible;
		margin-bottom: 10px;
	}

	.mpc-cycle-bar-fill {
		height: 100%;
		border-radius: 999px;
		background: linear-gradient(90deg, #2d6a4f, #74b49b);
		transition: width 0.4s ease;
	}

	.mpc-cycle-bar-marker {
		position: absolute;
		top: 50%;
		width: 16px;
		height: 16px;
		margin-left: -8px;
		margin-top: -8px;
		border-radius: 50%;
		background: #74b49b;
		border: 2px solid #0d1f17;
		box-shadow: 0 0 12px rgba(116, 180, 155, 0.5);
		transition: left 0.4s ease;
	}

	.mpc-cycle-bar-labels {
		display: flex;
		justify-content: space-between;
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 12px;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.4);
	}

	.mpc-stats-grid {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
		gap: 12px;
		width: 100%;
		margin-bottom: 28px;
	}

	@media (max-width: 560px) {
		.mpc-stats-grid {
			grid-template-columns: 1fr;
		}
	}

	.mpc-stat {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		align-items: center;
		gap: 6px;
		padding: 16px 12px;
		background: rgba(12, 12, 12, 0.5);
		border: 1px solid rgba(45, 106, 79, 0.2);
		border-radius: 12px;
	}

	.mpc-stat-value {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: clamp(16px, 3vw, 20px);
		font-weight: 800;
		background: linear-gradient(135deg, #2d6a4f, #74b49b);
		-webkit-background-clip: text;
		-webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
		background-clip: text;
		text-align: center;
		line-height: 1.2;
	}

	.mpc-stat-label {
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 11px;
		font-weight: 600;
		letter-spacing: 1px;
		text-transform: uppercase;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.45);
		text-align: center;
	}

	.mpc-upcoming {
		width: 100%;
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		gap: 12px;
	}

	.mpc-upcoming-row {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		gap: 4px;
		margin: 0;
		padding: 14px 16px;
		background: rgba(12, 12, 12, 0.4);
		border: 1px solid rgba(45, 106, 79, 0.15);
		border-radius: 10px;
	}

	.mpc-upcoming-label {
		font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
		font-size: 11px;
		font-weight: 600;
		letter-spacing: 1.5px;
		text-transform: uppercase;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.4);
	}

	.mpc-upcoming-date {
		font-family: 'Outfit', sans-serif;
		font-size: 15px;
		font-weight: 600;
		color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.75);
	}
</style>
